-------- Message original --------
Sujet: 	EPIA 2013 - Last CFP - 16th Portuguese Conference on Artificial 
Intelligence (deadline April 5th)
Date : 	Wed, 3 Apr 2013 10:03:01 +0100
De : 	Luis Paulo Reis <lpreis@dsi.uminho.pt>
Pour : 	organizadores epia2013 <epia2013@gmail.com>



----------------------------------------------------
EPIA’2013 – 16th Portuguese Conference on Artificial Intelligence
----------------------------------------------------
University of Azores, Portugal,
September 9-13, 2013,
http://www.epia2013.uac.pt/
Deadline for paper submission: April, 5th, 2013
Proceedings Published by Springer LNAI

----------------------------------------------------
Introduction
----------------------------------------------------
The 16th Portuguese Conference on Artificial Intelligence, EPIA'2013, 
will take place at the beautiful city of Angra do Heroísmo (world 
heritage) at Terceira Island at the University of Azores, Portugal in 
September 9th-13th, 2013.
As in previous years, this international conference is hosted with the 
patronage of the Portuguese Association for Artificial Intelligence 
(APPIA). The purpose of this conference is to promote research in all 
areas of Artificial Intelligence (AI), covering both 
theoretical/foundational issues and applications, and the scientific 
exchange among researchers, engineers and practitioners in related 
disciplines.

----------------------------------------------------
Conference Format
----------------------------------------------------
To promote discussions among participants, the coming conference is 
structured as a set of thematic tracks. In addition to the parallel 
technical sessions for the different tracks, there will be a special 
track, doctoral symposium, exhibitions and plenary sessions with invited 
lectures given by leading scientists:
* Ana Paiva (IST – Technical University of Lisbon, Portugal)
* Carla Gomes (Cornell University, USA)
* Kenneth O. Stanley(University of Central Florida, USA)
* Maria Fasli (University of Essex, UK)

----------------------------------------------------
Thematic Tracks
----------------------------------------------------
EPIA 2013, will have a set of thematic tracks intended to promote the 
different sub-areas of research within AI and the cross-fertilization of 
ideas between researchers of the different research groups. After 
evaluation of proposals received in response to the Call for Thematic 
Tracks, the following tracks were selected and included in the 
conference program:
* AI4GAMES – Artificial Intelligence Methodologies for Games
* AITS – Artificial Intelligence in Transportation Systems
* ALEA – Artificial Life and Evolutionary Algorithms
* AmIA – Ambient Intelligence and Affective Environments
* CMBSB – Computational Methods in Bioinformatics and Systems Biology
* GAI – General Artificial Intelligence
* IROBOT – Intelligent Robotics
* KDBI – Knowledge Discovery and Business Intelligence
* (m)AS&ILE – Agent Systems and Intelligent Learning Environments
* MASTA – Multi-agent Systems: Theory and Applications
* SSM – Social Simulation and Modelling
* TeMA – Text Mining and Applications

----------------------------------------------------
Challenges/Special Track
----------------------------------------------------
Azores is part of Macaronesia, a group of five archipelagos situated in 
the North Atlantic Ocean. In an attempt to improve knowledge about AI 
applications, the organizers decided to setup a special program in which 
scientific research problems related to islands and archipelagos, often 
linked to Regional Development, are  listed by researchers, while other 
researchers from Artificial Intelligence are invited to study and sketch 
some solutions for those problems. This Special Track embraces five 
different thematic “challenges”. Each challenge is related with research 
problems actively being tackled by researchers in the Azores.

----------------------------------------------------
Doctoral Symposium
----------------------------------------------------
The Doctoral Symposium on Artificial Intelligence - SDIA 2013, in its 
fourth edition, is a satellite event of EPIA 2013.  As in previous 
editions, SDIA 2013 aims at being a forum for discussion on 
post-graduated studies, thesis on Artificial Intelligence, increasing 
the integration and the cooperation between researchers from this 
scientific area and promoting a better visibility of their ongoing work 
to the academic and industrial communities. Several types of PhD student 
papers are welcome: full research papers, short papers, position papers 
(e.g. describing ongoing work without results) or thesis proposals.

----------------------------------------------------
Paper Submission and Publication
----------------------------------------------------
EPIA 2013 welcomes submissions of technical papers to the thematic 
tracks, special track and doctoral symposium. Submitted papers to the 
thematic tracks should present original, high-quality and previously 
unpublished results on Artificial Intelligence.
Papers should be prepared according to the formatting instructions of 
Springer LNAI series, with a maximum of 12 pages for full papers and 
submitted at: https://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=epia2013 by 
the submission deadline (April 5, 2013).
A selection of high quality full papers presented in the different 
tracks will be published by Springer, in a volume of the LNAI series. 
All remaining papers presented at the conference will be published in a 
conference proceedings book. At least one author must be registered, by 
the early registration deadline, in order for each paper to be published.

----------------------------------------------------
Important dates
----------------------------------------------------
* Deadline for paper submission: April 5, 2013
* Notification of paper acceptance: May 10, 2013
* Deadline for camera ready versions: May 31, 2013
* Conference dates: September 9-13, 2013

----------------------------------------------------
