      <br>
      <div dir="ltr">----------------------------------------------------<br>
        EPIA’2013 – 16th Portuguese Conference on Artificial
        Intelligence<br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        University of Azores, Portugal, <br>
        September 9-13, 2013,<br>
        <a moz-do-not-send="true" href="http://www.epia2013.uac.pt/">http://www.epia2013.uac.pt/</a><br>
        Deadline for paper submission: April, 5th, 2013<br>
        Proceedings Published by Springer LNAI<br>
        <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Introduction<br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        The 16th Portuguese Conference on Artificial Intelligence,
        EPIA'2013, will take place at the beautiful city of Angra do
        Heroísmo (world heritage) at Terceira Island at the University
        of Azores, Portugal in September 9th-13th, 2013. <br>
        As in previous years, this international conference is hosted
        with the patronage of the Portuguese Association for Artificial
        Intelligence (APPIA). The purpose of this conference is to
        promote research in all areas of Artificial Intelligence (AI),
        covering both theoretical/foundational issues and applications,
        and the scientific exchange among researchers, engineers and
        practitioners in related disciplines.<br>
        <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Conference Format<br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        To promote discussions among participants, the coming conference
        is structured as a set of thematic tracks. In addition to the
        parallel technical sessions for the different tracks, there will
        be a special track, doctoral symposium, exhibitions and plenary
        sessions with invited lectures given by leading scientists:<br>
        * Ana Paiva (IST – Technical University of Lisbon, Portugal)<br>
        * Carla Gomes (Cornell University, USA)<br>
        * Kenneth O. Stanley(University of Central Florida, USA)<br>
        * Maria Fasli (University of Essex, UK)<br>
        <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Thematic Tracks<br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        EPIA 2013, will have a set of thematic tracks intended to
        promote the different sub-areas of research within AI and the
        cross-fertilization of ideas between researchers of the
        different research groups. After evaluation of proposals
        received in response to the Call for Thematic Tracks, the
        following tracks were selected and included in the conference
        program:<br>
        * AI4GAMES – Artificial Intelligence Methodologies for Games<br>
        * AITS – Artificial Intelligence in Transportation Systems<br>
        * ALEA – Artificial Life and Evolutionary Algorithms<br>
        * AmIA – Ambient Intelligence and Affective Environments<br>
        * CMBSB – Computational Methods in Bioinformatics and Systems
        Biology<br>
        * GAI – General Artificial Intelligence<br>
        * IROBOT – Intelligent Robotics<br>
        * KDBI – Knowledge Discovery and Business Intelligence<br>
        * (m)AS&amp;ILE – Agent Systems and Intelligent Learning
        Environments<br>
        * MASTA – Multi-agent Systems: Theory and Applications<br>
        * SSM – Social Simulation and Modelling<br>
        * TeMA – Text Mining and Applications<br>
        <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Challenges/Special Track <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Azores is part of Macaronesia, a group of five archipelagos
        situated in the North Atlantic Ocean. In an attempt to improve
        knowledge about AI applications, the organizers decided to setup
        a special program in which scientific research problems related
        to islands and archipelagos, often linked to Regional
        Development, are  listed by researchers, while other researchers
        from Artificial Intelligence are invited to study and sketch
        some solutions for those problems. This Special Track embraces
        five different thematic “challenges”. Each challenge is related
        with research problems actively being tackled by researchers in
        the Azores. <br>
        <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Doctoral Symposium<br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        The Doctoral Symposium on Artificial Intelligence - SDIA 2013,
        in its fourth edition, is a satellite event of EPIA 2013.  As in
        previous editions, SDIA 2013 aims at being a forum for
        discussion on post-graduated studies, thesis on Artificial
        Intelligence, increasing the integration and the cooperation
        between researchers from this scientific area and promoting a
        better visibility of their ongoing work to the academic and
        industrial communities. Several types of PhD student papers are
        welcome: full research papers, short papers, position papers
        (e.g. describing ongoing work without results) or thesis
        proposals.<br>
        <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Paper Submission and Publication<br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        EPIA 2013 welcomes submissions of technical papers to the
        thematic tracks, special track and doctoral symposium. Submitted
        papers to the thematic tracks should present original,
        high-quality and previously unpublished results on Artificial
        Intelligence.<br>
        Papers should be prepared according to the formatting
        instructions of Springer LNAI series, with a maximum of 12 pages
        for full papers and submitted at: <a moz-do-not-send="true"
          href="https://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=epia2013">https://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=epia2013</a>
        by the submission deadline (April 5, 2013).<br>
        A selection of high quality full papers presented in the
        different tracks will be published by Springer, in a volume of
        the LNAI series. All remaining papers presented at the
        conference will be published in a conference proceedings book.
        At least one author must be registered, by the early
        registration deadline, in order for each paper to be published.<br>
        <br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        Important dates<br>
        ----------------------------------------------------<br>
        * Deadline for paper submission: April 5, 2013<br>
        * Notification of paper acceptance: May 10, 2013<br>
